&gt; An **isobar** is a **line drawn** on a weather map that `connects all points having the same atmospheric pressure` at a given time, usually reduced to sea level.

The word “isobar” comes from the Greek words *iso* (equal) and *baros* (weight or pressure). Isobars help meteorologists and geographers understand and predict atmospheric conditions by showing pressure distribution across large areas.
